<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-OFFBEAT-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FLOP OF A FORUM FAREWELL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Last one out of the Forum, turn out the lights.
</P>
<P>
   Oh, that's right. Tim Duncan already did....
</P>
<P>
   _Maybe you pick the San Antonio Spurs to rough up the Los
Angeles Lakers in six, but you don't expect the Lakers to look sick
in four....
</P>
<P>
   _The fans weren't booing, they were chanting ``Luuuuue.'' That
is, when they weren't chanting ``Eddie.... Eddie.''....
</P>
<P>
   _At least Tyronn Lue played with some heart and passion....
</P>
<P>
   _At the time it was a brilliant stroke of luck _ Kurt Rambis
turning down the Clippers on a head-coaching offer and then having
the Lakers hand one to him a few months later.
</P>
<P>
   As much as everyone was pulling for him to succeed, Rambo was
never able to pull the trigger. That was finally obvious when he
complained before Game 3 about the media not letting his team grow.
</P>
<P>
   Nap time, Kurt. It won't be the media who won't allow him room
to grow as a head coach. Team owners have a way of interceding....
</P>
<P>
   _Phil Jackson, please pick up the white courtesy phone....
</P>
<P>
   _Our stat sheet shows the Lakers still have a foul to give,
which might carry over to the Staples Center opener....
</P>
<P>
   _A superb public-relations move, Magic Johnson admitting his
interest in someday assuming ownership of the Lakers. Just at a
time when another outside distraction was the last thing the team
needed and Magic needed to draw some attention....
</P>
<P>
   _Here's hoping the Chicago Bulls make the playoffs every year
from now on so the public isn't subjected to the bloated Jerry
Krause rubbing his greedy hands together at NBA draft lottery time.
All Krause was missing was the sequined jumpsuit....
</P>
<P>
   _We're banking on the fact Pascual Perez drives a cab now in
Atlanta and will give Michael Ovitz a lift to the NFL owners
meetings....
</P>
<P>
   _Did you see Ovitz's plan for frosted-glass windows around the
roof of the renovated Coliseum? That'll stay fresh for about 20
minutes....
</P>
<P>
   _Eli Broad is gonna tell the owners that his 60,000-seat version
of the Coliseum will sell out each game, so they don't have to
worry about blackouts. How will he do that? He'll make up the
difference if ticket sales stink....
</P>
<P>
   _The formation of Major League Lacrosse, a new pro outdoor
league not to be confused with the indoor National Lacrosse League,
will be announced today.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles has already expressed acute indifference but expects
the league to come begging soon, at which time it will show
absolutely no interest at all....
</P>
<P>
   _Your inflated insurance rates at work: Allstate has bought the
naming rights to Chicago's Rosemont Horizon. Terms were not
disclosed, but there's likely a $5 million deductible....
</P>
<P>
   _Chin-Feng Chen, the Taiwanese outfielder the Dodgers have on
display at their Single-A San Bernardino team, is hitting .340 with
seven homers and 37 RBI in 38 games....
</P>
<P>
   _Was the opening of Fox's ``Phantom Menace'' a menace to Fox's
Dodgers fandom last Wednesday?
</P>
<P>
   Put it this way: With Kevin Brown throwing against the team with
the best record in the National League, the Dodgers forced 26,360
to come on in against the Houston Astros _ a 32 percent drop from
their season average prior to that day of 38,669. And there was a
Lakers playoff game, albeit on television, the same night going
head-to-head.
</P>
<P>
   For what it's worth, 12 of the 14 teams that hosted a game
Wednesday saw an attendance slump. In New York, the Mets' game was
rained out....
</P>
<P>
   _Meanwhile, in a galaxy far, far away from first place in Major
League Soccer....
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
