<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXYNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HERMOSILLO'S RETURN MAY PROVIDE BOOST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Los Angeles Galaxy general manager Sergio Del
Prado hopes that Mexican scoring champion Carlos Hermosillo will
report soon and be ready for Los Angeles' next game at the Rose
Bowl, June 6 against Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   Hermosillo's Mexican club team, Necaxa, was eliminated from the
Mexican League playoffs Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He (Hermosillo) is looking for about a week off,'' Del Prado
said. ``He spoke to Sigi (Schmid) two weeks ago and indicated that
he would need at least one week to get himself going again.
</P>
<P>
   ``At this point, we're hopeful we'll have him here against
Kansas City.''
</P>
<P>
   With the Galaxy in the worst scoring drought in club history
before Sunday's game against New England (five goals, nine games),
Del Prado feels the Hermosillo will give Los Angeles a much-needed
spark.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know the team is looking for him to come in and turn some
things around,'' Del Prado said. ``If you look at our forwards,
everyone is fast and quick. We don't have a physical presence, but
that's what Carlos will bring us.''
</P>
<P>
   Elliott comes aboard: New Zealand national team midfielder Simon
Elliott joined the Galaxy on Saturday, becoming the team's fourth
foreign-allocated player after the club waived 17-year-old
Ecuadoran Jaime Caicedo last week.
</P>
<P>
   Elliott, who has been training with the Galaxy this past week,
was in uniform Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are very happy to add Simon to our roster,'' Schmid said.
``He is very good with either foot and can play anywhere in the
midfield. He is not a typical player coming out of college, having
gained plenty of international experience with the New Zealand
national team.''
</P>
<P>
   Schmid is aware of what Elliott can do. The 24-year-old faced
Schmid's UCLA teams while playing at Stanford.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-24-99 0215EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
