<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    News For Kids Websites
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Flit and flutter
</P>
<P>
   Do you like to chase butterflies? Before you trap that butterfly
in your net, learn more about these beautiful creatures on the Net
at www.mesc.usgs.gov/butterfly/butterfly.html. The Children's
Butterfly site provides tons of information about butterflies and
moths. The coloring page explains the life cycle of the monarch and
tells how you can raise your own caterpillar. Print out pages to
color and visit the multiple links.
</P>
<P>
   _ Anne Y. Meyers
</P>
<P>
   You wanted to know . . .
</P>
<P>
   Roberta McQuade's sixth-grade social studies class at Ridgeview
Elementary wanted more information on a news flash from May 17. Her
student Winsley Felix e-mailed, ``Our class has just finished
reading the NFK story on eye-scans to ID (bank) customers. We want
to know what happens if you wear contact lenses?'' The kids in
Fulton County can rest easy now _ we found out the answer. ``It
works with contact lenses, glasses and most sunglasses,'' explains
bank spokesman Vern Stockton. But, he says, you'll have to take off
your mirrored glasses _ those won't work.
</P>
<P>
   _ Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
</P>
<P>
   We love Greg Maddux
</P>
<P>
   You can find your favorite Braves pitcher in the June issue of
Sports Illustrated for Kids (which hits the racks today for $2.99).
Featuring five full pages about Greg Maddux, the issue also offers
a pull0out poster of this four-time Cy Young Award winner. You'll
find out his nickname, his favorite part of the game and see him as
a young boy trying to hit. You can get a sneak peek at the story at
www.sikids.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
</P>
