<HEADLINE>
BOOKS RECENTLY REVIEWED IN THE BOSTON GLOBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ?????  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Close Range: Wyoming Stories'' by Annie Proulx (Scribner,
$25). Tales of folks and life as sharp and spiky as barbed wire. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Identity's Architect: A Biography of Erik H. Erikson'' by
Lawrence J. Friedman (Scribner, $35). A detailed and panoramic life
of a faded culture hero. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
