<HEADLINE>
A GRILL FOR ALL SEASONS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ Summertime and the livin' is easy ... time to
relax with books and barbecuing.
</P>
<P>
   But don't fret if you live in an apartment and don't have room
for an outdoor grill that runs on liquid propane, natural gas or
charcoal briquettes.
</P>
<P>
   Keep that barbecue marinade at the ready, because T-Fal Corp. of
New Jersey has designed smokeless indoor grills to make barbecuing
a timeless indoor convenience.
</P>
<P>
   The Excelio Indoor grills are designed to sear meats and other
foods instantly, locking in their natural juices. The grills also
feature family-size removable cooking plates with T-Fal nonstick
coating for healthier, low-fat cooking and easy cleanups.
Smoke-free cooking is possible because the unit's heating element
is nested in a protective groove under the heavy gauge
cast-aluminum grill plate.
</P>
<P>
   In turn, the nonstick ridged grill plate channels fats and
excess juices away from the food and heating element, preventing
smoke or flare-ups that happen when fat comes in contact with the
heat source.
</P>
<P>
   To operate the grill, pour about one quart of water into the
removable drip tray, plug in, preheat for approximately 10 minutes
and you're ready to cook.
</P>
<P>
   The Multi-Grill Excelio BBQ+Griddle by T-Fal features an
interchangeable nonstick coated griddle plate for cooking pancakes,
French toast, bacon, eggs, home fries and other breakfast and
brunch food.
</P>
<P>
   Both grills feature adjustable thermostats, on/off indicator
lights, cool-to-the-touch handles, fully removable, dishwasher-safe
drip trays and nonstick grill plates.
</P>
<P>
   The T-Fal Excelio Indoor BBQ retails for $89.99 and the Excelio
Indoor BBQ+Griddle for $109.99. Both come with full-color recipe
and instruction booklets.
</P>
<P>
   For further information, visit the company's Web site at
http://www.t-fal.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
