protected by the Fourth Amendment when they let TV camera crews and
other journalists accompany them on so-called ``media ride-alongs''
into private homes to observe arrests or searches, the Supreme
Court decides. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   PRESIDENT-SALARY (Washington) _ A House panel holds a hearing on
doubling the president's salary from $200,000 to $400,000 annually.
Proponents note that presidents' salaries haven't been raised since
1969. Any boost would take effect after Bill Clinton leaves office.
By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
