<HEADLINE>
`INSOMNIA' MAGNIFICENT; `ALICE' IS WONDERFUL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Insomnia'' _ One of the best foreign films of
the past few years features Stellan Skarsgard as a Swedish
inspector investigating a murder case near the Arctic Circle. Grim.
Bleak. Magnificent. Director Erik Skjoldbjaerg maintains a dramatic
artistry not often seen in current films.
</P>
<P>
   ``Alice in Wonderland'' _ Whoopi Goldberg, Martin Short, Ben
Kingsley, George Wendt, Gene Wilder, and Christopher Lloyd have a
surrealistic ball in the marvelous adaptation of Lewis Carroll's
novel, originally broadcast on NBC. The effects, created by the Jim
Henson Creature Shop, are imaginative. This edition is 20 minutes
shorter than the broadcast _ which actually makes it better.
Finally, a Robert (``Gulliver's Travels'') Halmi production that's
both a critical and commercial success.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: ``The Avengers'' was a bust on the big screen, but
the original TV show has been a big hit on home video. ``The
Avengers '67,'' a digitally remastered boxed set featuring 12
episodes from the 1967 season, is a must for any fan of Steed and
Peel. . . . Barney's first DVD, ``Let's Play School!,'' will
feature five programs on one disc. According to Lyrick Studios, the
DVD will include an audio program, ``A Great Day for Learning''; an
electronic book, ``Barney's ABC Animals''; and five Windows CD-ROM
games along with the title disc. It retails for $24.99 and will be
available in late July.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: June 1: ``Berenstain Bears'' (three new
episodes), ``The Base,'' ``Gunshy.'' June 8: ``From the Earth to
the Moon,'' ``Treehouse Hostage,'' ``Psycho'' (remake), ``Gods and
Monsters,'' ``Before Stonewall,'' ``After Stonewall,'' ``Last
Rites.'' June 15: ``Little Voice,'' ``The World Within,'' ``Enemy
of the State,'' ``The Faculty,'' ``Facade,'' ``The Patriot.'' June
22: ``Waking Ned Devine,'' ``Patch Adams,'' ``A Simple Plan,''
``Rushmore,'' ``Wishful Thinking,'' ``Sweethearts,'' ``The Life of
Birds,'' ``Storm of the Century.'' June 29: ``The Thin Red Line,''
``Varsity Blues,'' ``Lansky.''
</P>
