<P>
   COURT-HARASS (Washington) _ School systems around the country
are put on notice that they must stop students from sexually
harassing their classmates or face costly lawsuits and damage
payments. The Supreme Court rules 5-4 that teachers and
administrators who fail to stop such behavior may be violating a
federal anti-bias law. By MARK HELM. (1stLd-Writethru of story
filed earlier.)
</P>
<P>
