   NASCAR
</P>
<P>
   CAR-STEWART _ It will be an interesting set of logistics on
Saturday for NASCAR rookie Tony Stewart, who will run the Indy 500
in the morning and the Charlotte 600 NASCAR race that night.
(Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-CARTER _ Claiming he was burned out, Quincy Carter says he
won't go back to baseball this summer and will instead give all his
time to getting ready for Georgia football. He has changed agents,
dropping Lonnie Cooper for Eugene Parker. Parker is the agent for
Deion Sanders. Carter says he has not completely closed the door on
resuming his baseball career next year. He remains property of the
Chicago Cubs. (Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-AUBURN-SUIT _ Former assistant football coach Bill Oliver
files fraud suit against Auburn University, top supporter Bobby
Lowder and AD David Housel. Oliver contends he was misled by Lowder
and Housel, and it cost him money and jobs. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Contitution). 13-15.
</P>
<P>
   MISCELLANEOUS
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS _ NUMBERS _ What's in a number? Almost everything, if
you're into sports. You say 8, I say Yogi, some guy in Athens says
_ Buck Belue? Well, yes. You say 23, we all say Michael. On some
numbers, we can agree that they are the one and only. For most
others, we have our personal preferences, or rank them 1-2-3. Gold,
silver and bronze. From 00 to 99, umbers say a lot about our
sporting makeup: who we are, where we grew up, our ages and
stations in life. ... While we associate greatness with specific
numbers, some numbers also evoke sporting moments and milestones,
favorite athletes or unforgettable teams. These are numbers we mark
our lives by. (Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
DOUBLE-TRUCK LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   WEB-SPORTS _ There is a cross section of American sports fans
who have lived two lives _ Pre-Web and Post-Web. The Internet has
become a way of life for many fans, fundamentally changing and
enriching lifelong habits. Now you can: listen to any major league
baseball game broadcast at any time; access up-to-the-second sports
news including current developments in every ongoing game in every
sport; instantly converse with other sports fans from all parts of
the world. (Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
