   SCOTUS-SKOL-HARASS _ The U.S. Supreme Court on Monday, deciding
in a Monroe County, Ga., said that school boards can be sued if
educators show a ``deliberate indifference'' to complaints of one
student sexually harassing another. (Rankin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
