   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   GORE _ ATLANTA _ Just days after six students were wounded at a
suburban high school, Vice President Al Gore delivers a major
speech on values at a Salvation Army cafeteria in Atlanta. The
speech is the top-billed event of a three-day trip that includes
stops in Florida and Texas. Gore plans to visit students and
parents at Heritage High, scene of last week's school shooting,
after his speech late this afternoon. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
