   GENEALOGY-WEBSITE _ A Web site put together by the Mormon church
lists 400 million names of people who lived as long ago as 1500,
many of them with pedigree charts. The site, www.familysearch.org,
is a genealogist's dream. (LizLee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DDN-COX-WILKINS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ A federal appeals court Friday
reinstated a lawsuit accusing state officials of defrauding the
government by not reporting the misuse of federal anti-poverty
funds. The 6th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals returned Terry
Wilkins' lawsuit to the U.S. District in Columbus, which had
dismissed it in February 1997. (Bennish, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   THERAPY _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Hospitals aren't the only
victims of federal Medicare cuts. The 1997 reductions capped
payments for patients using physical therapy and rehabilitation
centers to $1,500 a year. Centers associated with hospitals are
exempt from the caps. At least one local company is laying off some
therapists, checking on others. (Murawski, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
