holds police liable for letting TV crews film in people's homes,
the Los Angeles Police Department suspended taping of ``LAPD _ Life
on the Beat'' in March. The city is fighting two lawsuits that
contend the Los Angeles police allowed camera crews to violate
people's privacy. By Peter Hartlaub. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
