<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JBAKER-REPP-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
J. BAKER REVISES STRATEGIC PLAN WITH REPP ACQUISITION 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By CHRIS REIDY  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   J. Baker Inc. said Monday its acquisition of Repp Ltd., a
175-store apparel chain for big and tall men, will revise its
previously announced strategic plan.
</P>
<P>
   J. Baker already operates several retail chains including Casual
Male Big &AMP; Tall, which accounted for nearly half of the company's
$584.3 million in sales last year.
</P>
<P>
   Nearly a year ago, J. Baker said it would open a second big and
tall chain aimed at a more affluent customer. The new chain was to
have been called Grande Central.
</P>
<P>
   Monday J. Baker said it would ``no longer proceed'' with Grande
Central because the Repp acquisition would achieve many of the same
goals, only at a faster pace.
</P>
<P>
   ``It would have taken time to build a name and a mailing list''
for a new chain, said J. Baker president and chief executive Alan
I. Weinstein.
</P>
<P>
   The Repp acquisition will do that right away and will be
``accretive'' to J. Baker's earnings, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Repp will keep its name and its merchandising team, but Repp and
Casual Male plan to combine some back-office functions.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this month, J. Baker said it intended to pay $31.7
million in cash to Edison Brothers Stores Inc., Repp's bankrupt
operator.
</P>
<P>
   Problems with its other chains were what caused Edison's woes;
the Repp division is profitable, Weinstein said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think they got a heck of a buy,'' said Buckingham Research
Group analyst Lee F. Backus of J. Baker's purchase of Repp. ``This
is a terrific opportunity.''
</P>
<P>
   Repp had sales of roughly $100 million last year. Casual Male
had sales of about $270 million, Weinstein said.
</P>
<P>
   With Repp and Casual Male joining forces, J. Baker will become
one of the biggest players in the highly fragmented $6 billion
market for big and tall men's clothing, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Plans also call for Casual Male to sharply increase the number
of outlet stores it operates. In five years, the chain could
operate as many as 250 outlet stores. That would make J. Baker a
major presence in the three major price categories of the men's big
and tall market _ discount, moderate, and upscale.
</P>
<P>
   J. Baker has had its ups and downs in recent years as it has
become less reliant on retail footwear, once its core business. In
its latest quarter, earnings were hurt by unseasonably warm
weather, which slowed sales for fall and winter merchandise.
</P>
<P>
   Some of the capital J. Baker used for the Repp deal was provided
by BankBoston Retail Finance and Back Bay Capital LLC.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are confident that this new financing will enable (J.
Baker) to accomplish their strategic objectives,'' said Edward J.
Siskin, president of Back Bay Capital.
</P>
<P>
   On Nasdaq, J. Baker shares closed up 9/32, to 8 1/8. J. Baker
headquarters are in Canton, Mass.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
