<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-INDEPENDENT-PAPER-SOLD-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Alternative newspaper sold
 &HT;    By Jim Dillon
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Impact Weekly , Dayton's major alternative
newspaper, has been sold pending shareholder approval.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Epton, co-publisher of Impact Weekly , said the paper's
board has approved its sale to a subsidiary of Yesse!
Communications Inc. of Indianapolis, a publisher of four
alternative weeklies in Indiana, Illinois and Iowa. The board will
ask shareholders June 1 to approve the sale, said Jeff Epton,
Impact Weekly's co-publisher.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed. Yesse!, however, plans to
invest about $300,000 in Impact Weekly over the next 18 months so
it can hire more staff and boost its coverage, Epton said. The free
newspaper has a circulation of about 24,000, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The proposed deal calls for all Impact Weekly staffers,
including Epton and co-publisher Marrianne McMullen, to be
retained.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, the masthead changes, but Jeff and Marrianne will
remain very much in charge'' of local operations, said Craig
Hitchcock, chairman and chief executive of Yesse! Communications.
</P>
<P>
   The paper will retain its ``edgy'' editorial format, but the
range and depth of editorial content will increase, Hitchcock and
Epton said.
</P>
<P>
   Impact Weekly, formerly known as the Dayton Voice , started
publication in August 1993. Epton said he has mixed feelings about
selling the newspaper, which remains unprofitable.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody feels a little bit of regret. Certainly, if we had a
little more money or made some smarter decisions earlier, it might
be a different story,'' Epton said. ``But it's a positive thing for
us, and I hope it's a positive thing for those who read the
paper.''
</P>
<P>
   Jim Dillon writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
