   (NYT25) VIETRI SUL MARE, Italy -- May 24, 1999 --
ITALY-ECO-MONSTER, 5-24 -- Dante Mazzitelli, the owner of the Hotel
Fuente, which was labeled one of Italy's 10 most hideous
``eco-monsters'' by Italy's largest conservation group, walks past
the hotel which is being demolished. The hotel, overlooking the
Amalfi Coast, is only one of hundreds of similar illegal
constructions that go up every year in Italy. But the hotel's
infamously jarring modern architectural style set on one of Italy's
most picturesque coasts has made it an international cause celebre.
(James Hill/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
