<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBC-UTEXAS-NCAATOURNAMENT-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Texas makes 64-team field for NCAA tournament
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ After Texas players and coaches were rewarded a
berth in the NCAA baseball playoffs Monday, they received an
encouraging message from someone who knows about second chances.
</P>
<P>
   Texas football coach Mack Brown, whose own team started 1-2,
rebounded with one of the most memorable seasons in a decade. There
is no reason the baseball team can't have a similar finish, Brown
told the players after they watched the selection show on TV.
</P>
<P>
   Texas, staggered by a 1-7 finish, is one of six Big 12 teams
invited to the 64-team NCAA regionals.
</P>
<P>
   Texas (35-24) will be the No. 3 seed in a regional at the
University of Houston. The Longhorns will play No. 2 seed
Southwestern Louisiana (38-22) at 3 p.m. Friday. Top seed Houston
(38-22) will play No. 4 Southwest Texas State (27-30) at 7 p.m.
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The double-elimination tournament will continue through Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Now that we've got the good news, we don't have to worry any
more,'' Texas catcher Sam Anderson said. ``Like Coach Brown said,
we have a great opportunity in front of us, and it's up to us to
take advantage of it.''
</P>
<P>
   Big 12 teams invited to the regionals are Texas A&AMP;M, Texas Tech,
Baylor, Nebraska, Oklahoma State and Texas. Missing from the mix is
Missouri, which made a strong bid by winning 11 of its last 13
games.
</P>
<P>
   The Texas-Missouri debate most likely was determined by the
latest RPI poll. The Longhorns, who played one of the toughest
schedules in the country, are No. 31 in the poll. Missouri is No.
50.
</P>
<P>
   ``The players earned it with the schedule they played and the
games they won,'' Texas Coach Augie Garrido said. ``They're in the
tournament as a result of their power rating. I don't think this is
a gift. It's something they earned.''
</P>
<P>
   Texas has a 28-3 series advantage over Southwestern Louisiana,
the Sun Belt Conference champion. The Ragin' Cajuns finished their
season last weekend with consecutive losses. Texas and USL are
unranked.
</P>
<P>
   The Big 12 and the Southeastern Conference landed six teams
apiece in the field. The Atlantic Coast Conference had five and the
Pac-10 four.
</P>
<P>
   The winner of the Houston regional will be paired against the
winner of the regional in Lubbock. That regional includes host
Texas Tech (40-15), Rice (52-11), Wisconsin-Milwaukee (30-27) and
Rutgers (37-19).
</P>
<P>
   Rick Cantu writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
