<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-FBC-UCLA-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UCLA ANNOUNCES FOOTBALL, BASKETBALL SIGNINGS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ The UCLA men's basketball team announced it has
signed Spencer Gloger, a 6-foot-6 wing man from Santa Margarita
High. Gloger initially committed to Princeton, but a financial
issue forced him to change plans. (Ivy League schools provide
grants, not full scholarships.) A solid shooter and ballhandler,
Gloger is the second player to sign scholarship papers with UCLA
this month, behind Artesia High star Jason Kapono.
</P>
<P>
   In football, UCLA has received an oral commitment from
 &UR; !bold! &LR; Albert Hollis, a tailback from Christian Brothers High in
Sacramento. He had scholarship offers from Cal, USC and Nebraska,
according to Student Sports Magazine. Hollis is the fourth prep
junior to commit to UCLA for the 1999-2000 recruiting season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
