ying out to be munchkings in The Wizard of Oz. By BILL GOODYKOON
TZ. Story will move in the ``L'' category.  &QL; 
TALIESIN - No, the Wright Brothers did not live at Taliesin West.
This was the enclave of famed American architect Frank Lloyd
Wright, who founded a school of architecture there 60 years ago
that still thrives. But this is also a favorite destination for
tourists, who enjoy any number of tours every day of the week that
encompass the 600-acre historic landmark. Summer hours begin June
1. By BARBARA YOST. Photographs by MARK HENLE. Story will move in
the ``L'' category.  &QL; 
